{
    "analysis": "We inspected metrics and traces for the five candidate services. What has been done: 1) Computed global P95/P5 thresholds per (service, KPI) across the full metric series; 2) Filtered metric data to the incident window and identified anomalies. Findings so far: recommendationservice shows elevated latency (latency-50 and latency-90), increased workload and some CPU elevation during the window; trace data shows high request volume (row_count up to 555) and elevated duration_p95 for recommendationservice (max ~2.3s). Productcatalogservice shows a metric anomaly labeled 'error' with high severity (severity 5.0) but its trace latencies for recommendation-related calls are very small, suggesting productcatalogservice responded quickly to recommendationservice calls. error_logs.csv contains 46 rows from 'frontend' reporting repeated \"failed to get product recommendations\" with RPC Unavailable at timestamps 1705357839–1705357846 (inside the incident window). Interpretation so far: traces point to recommendationservice experiencing latency under load; frontend RPC Unavailable errors reference product recommendations, consistent with recommendationservice being the downstream service impacting frontend. The productcatalogservice 'error' metric needs validation via logs because trace latencies indicate it is likely not the downstream failing service. Next we must inspect application logs for recommendationservice, productcatalogservice, and frontend during the incident window to confirm which service logged errors or RPC failures, and to check whether socket/network errors appear in logs.",
